{{Politics of Estonia}}
An '''[[independence referendum]]''' was held in [[Estonia]] on 3 March 1991,<ref name=DN>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p574 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> alongside a similar referendum in [[Latvian Soviet Socialist Republic|Latvia]] [[Latvian independence and democracy referendum, 1991|the same month]]. It was approved by 78.4% of voters with an 82.9% turnout. Independence was restored by the Estonian Supreme Council on the night of 20 August.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p567</ref>
==Results== Voters were asked "Do you want the restoration of the national independence and sovereignty of the Republic of Estonia?"<ref>{{cite web|title=Otsus referendumi korraldamise kohta Eesti Vabariigi iseseisvuse taastamise küsimuses|url=https://www.riigiteataja.ee/akt/30348|website=riigiteataja|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Restoration of the independence of Estonia, 1991|url=https://www.riigikogu.ee/en/press-releases/restoration-of-the-independence/|website=riigikogu.ee|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref> {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Choice !Votes !% |- |align=left|For||737,964||78.4 |- |align=left|Against||203,199||21.6 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||6,967||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''948,130'''||'''100''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||1,144,309||82.9 |- |align=left colspan=3|Source: [[Riigi Teataja]]<ref>{{cite web|title=1991. aasta 3. märtsil Eesti Vabariigi iseseisvuse taastamise küsimuses korraldatud referendumi tulemuse kinnitamise kohta|url=https://www.riigiteataja.ee/akt/13069820|publisher=[[Riigi Teataja]]|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref> |}
